Name: Derrel's Mini Storage, Inc
Category: Self Storage, Cold Storage Warehouses, Public & Commercial Warehouses
general_info: The Ridenours, Derrel J. and Derrel A. had a family-run stair and ornamental iron business in Fresno, Calif. In the early 1960's the business was asked to relocate to make way for a new freeway leaving its property at the northeast corner of Herndon and Villa vacant. To keep the property active, the two created Derrel s Mini Storage and decided to build fences and rent the space as contractor yards and storage for recreational vehicles. In 1963, using their knowledge of the ornamental iron business, they designed and built their first enclosed storage units constructed of wrought iron and sheet metal. Derrel's Mini Storage has more than 50 locations in central California including Bakersfield, Fresno, Clovis, Tulare, Visalia, Stockton, Modesto, Merced, San Luis Obispo and Sacramento, Calif.

Name: All About Storage
Category: Self Storage, Automobile Storage, Cold Storage Warehouses
general_info:
Whether you need to store boxes, furniture or business inventory, All About Storage has room for your belongings. Standard unit sizes range from 5'x5' to 10'x30', with an average ceiling height of 8 feet. 
  
 Drive-Up Storage Units 
 These ground-floor units are usually the size of a one-car garage, although several sizes can be available in the same facility. They feature a roll-up door, making for easy loading and unloading. Drive-up units are popular among: Businesses as a way of expanding their square footage for storage of files, equipment, etc. Retail stores for storage of seasonal inventory, signage, etc. Storage of cars, small-engine vehicles, tools, furniture, appliances and anything else that might be stored in a garage Indoor Storage Units 
 These units are part of a building, and are accessible by entering through doors and using elevators between floors. These units more sheltered from the elements than drive-up units. They are typically smaller, and have swing doors. They offer some additional security, and they are well-lit. 
 Indoor storage units are popular among: Customers who prefer to store their belongings in a house-like setting rather than a garage Pharmaceutical representatives, antiques dealers, and those with electronics, artwork or other valuable items who require a climate-controlled environment

general_info: For over 35 years, Storage West has been committed to providing a first-class storage experience for an excellent community of renters. We think who stores next to you is just as important as who you choose to store with. Storage West was formed in 1978 to fill the need for first class storage in the West. What makes us unique is that all our facilities are in the Western US, because we believe the West is a great place to live and to do business. Our goal is to provide clean, safe and secure facilities for families and businesses to store their belongings. We have an in-house call center staffed by trained Storage West employees. Our aim is to help our customers find what they're looking for faster. We are constantly looking at ways we can improve what we do. We're proud to have what we think is the best community of renters in the industry and those renters in turn refer great renters to us. Often a business will be overstocked and have a need for additional space. Many businesses use Storage West for their storage needs. With high levels of security and convenience, we give your business peace of mind. With our Business P.A.S.S. program, shipping services such as UPS and FedEx can deliver to your storage unit without requiring your presence. All the cool companies are doing it. Get rid of your office clutter and get that open layout office concept you drool over in Dwell magazine. Your storage requirements are going to be different than other businesses. Our storage professionals will work with you to determine and meet your unique needs. Many people own more than one vehicle and often storage can be an issue. Perhaps you have a sports car or a classic car that you bought as an investment. In the meantime, what do you do with it? Alternatively, you may have an extra car that you are currently not using. Do you want to leave it exposed to the elements? Perhaps you only live for part of the year in this area and you want to leave your car here when you are gone. One option is to put your vehicle in storage with Storage West. If you are considering vehicle storage there are some options. You can choose between outdoor storage and a drive-up storage unit. You can also choose air cooled storage if you have a smaller vehicle such as a motorcycle or ATV. Air cooled storage is an additional option for smaller vehicles such as vehicle parts, motorcycles, dirt bikes, ATVs etc. This means that your vehicle will be stored in a cooler temperature during hot weather which will prevent heat damage. This type of enclosed environment also keeps dust and dirt at bay. Then of course there are your residential storage needs. Whether you need to store some furniture during a move or remodeling project, or if you just need a little extra space for holiday décor, seasonal clothing, sports equipment, lawn equipment and other household items that need a little breathing room. Whatever your need, you can count on Storage West to provide a clean and protected environment. Thank you for choosing Storage West.

general_info: Budway Enterprises provides rail-transloading, inventory management and distribution services in Southern California. Located in Fontana, Calif., Budway is served by the Burlington Northern Santa Fe and the Union Pacific railroads and has five rail spurs able to spot 60 railcars simultaneously. The company has equipment to transload materials from boxcars, coil cars, center beam, flat cars and gondolas. It loads and delivers import materials from the break-bulk berths of both the Los Angeles and Long Beach harbors. Budway has two 30-ton overhead cranes and can transload using a number of lifts, including a 50,000-pound exterior forklift and a variety of boxcar lifts with capacities from 5,000 to 30,000 pounds. Materials can be stored in Budway s 17-acre yard or in its 120,000-square-foot warehouse. The company delivers products with its own truck fleet.

general_info: Welcome to Ag Futures Alliance The Ag Futures Alliance ( AFA ) is a county-based collaboration between farmers, ranchers, farm-workers, conservationists, and civic leaders who share a desire to build a vibrant, healthy, and durable food system. The first Ag Futures Alliance was started in 2000 in Ventura County, California when leaders in the farming community decided to engage farming critics in process of sharing views, trust-building, and ultimately identification of common ground. In the years since the founding of the AFA movement, new alliances have been formed in Ventura, Santa Barbara, and Yolo Counties. Ag Innovations Network ( AIN ) is proud to be the sponsor and facilitator of the pioneering Ventura AFA and the AFA project. Our goal is to create a network of AFA s across the state of California that ultimately can link efforts to more effectively improve local, state and federal policies that impact agriculture, the food system, and the environment.

general_info: At Stevens Worldwide, we believe in letting our reputation speak for itself. With over 110 years in business and 15,000 families moved each year, Stevens has earned its place as one of the nation's best household moving companies. Designed to meet your family's unique household moving needs and budget, our highly trained experts offer a full suite of moving services that ensure the safe transport and delivery of your belongings. From cross country to out of state moves, packing to storage, the team at Stevens is dedicated to helping you and your family complete a hassle-free transition. Stevens Worldwide Van Lines was established in 1905 in Saginaw, Michigan. Founder Frederick H. Stevens, Jr. used a single horse and dray to haul baggage to and from the Michigan Central Passenger Depot. Stevens is now a full-service moving company with more than 125 agent locations throughout the United States and has a division specifically dedicated to international relocations and general cargo shipments. Stevens performs local moves, long-distance moves and international moves with storage options for all types of relocations. Stevens also has special services for records storage and records management at many of its locations. Stevens Van Lines has continued under leadership of the same family for its entire history, and still maintains its headquarters in Saginaw. Members of the fourth and fifth generations of the company's founder continue to hold executive positions in the van line. Stevens is recognized as a ProMover by the American Moving & Storage Association. The ProMover program promotes ethical principles in the moving and storage industry and works with federal and state governments to eliminate unethical moving practices. ProMover status clearly separates professional movers from rogue operators posing as legitimate movers. To qualify as a ProMover, movers must pass a rigorous review of professional business standards. Stevens has an Employee Stock Ownership Plan (ESOP), with Morrison Stevens, Sr., Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer, owning 70% of the company and employees owning the remaining 30%. Because of their ownership, employees in ESOP companies tend to have more dedication to their work and are more dedicated to quality and customer satisfaction than employees who do not have an ownership interest in their employer. Stevens Mission: Stevens is the leader in the relocation industry and sets the standards for service, quality, value and customer commitment as well as investment and support of its employees and partners. Stevens Quality Policy: The Stevens Group will deliver Total Customer Satisfaction at a value that meets customer agreed-upon terms and conditions. Stevens is The Way to Move through our commitment to be the industry leader in providing quality driven consumer and corporate relocation services with quantifiable results.
